into a specialty, be it health systems or

03:03.391 --> 03:16.428
transportation or whatever. And it seems like the 
role of the generalist planner, which

03:22.126 --> 03:29.516
at least used to be what planners were, that they 
knew a process and therefore could apply it to

03:22.126 --> 03:29.516
anything. I think that we've been outrun by our 
legal people. I find that most planning decisions

03:35.885 --> 03:47.841
and policy decisions that are made in a number of 
cities, including this one, that are planning

03:35.885 --> 03:47.841
