04:17.464 --> 04:21.327
that I work with, and he and I And I deal policy. He 
deals legal. But it's a shame. I have not met very

04:26.536 --> 04:28.719
many. I'm a transportation planner. I'm a health 
planner. I've never said shit. Well, you remember

04:33.345 --> 04:39.433
in comprehensive planning, you talked about the 
concept of the hyphenated planner. Yes. You'd

04:40.133 --> 04:44.859
have the transportation hyphen planner, the 
health hyphen planner, the whatever hyphen

04:40.133 --> 04:44.859
planner. But who are the planner planners? That's 
the question you're asking. Where have they gone?

04:51.513 --> 04:54.816
Are we training any today in the universities? 
What is your perception of the recent grads from

04:54.836 --> 05:04.386
the Texas planning schools? Well, most of them are 
specialists, and that's fine. I've not been very

05:10.492 --> 05:14.175
impressed with them. I have interviewed a number 
of people, They're very intense about what

05:17.298 --> 05:27.350
they're doing, but they're very myopic about what

05:17.298 --> 05:27.350
they're doing. It reminds me of engineers a little 
bit.

05:33.638 --> 05:37.763
You know, you give somebody a situation and then 
they'll say, well, what they need is this service.

05:37.803 --> 05:44.031
They may not need that service, but that's what 
they were taught to do. A health plan. Well, they

05:45.593 --> 05:46.714
need dental care. Low-income people need dental 
care. Low-income people need money. They don't

05:50.614 --> 05:51.515
need dental care. Fuck the dental care. Go get the 
money as it is. That's the kind of thing. I think

05:57.422 --> 06:00.045
people don't cut through the bullshit. I think 
we've become isolated unto ourselves with our own

06:00.886 --> 06:15.705
little vocabulary at a time when you've got to 
explain to people that a council person who may be a

06:00.886 --> 06:15.705
developer or maybe something doesn't understand 
the kinds of things that the planners talk about.

06:20.347 --> 06:22.069
And I think you pick up vocabularies. I speak HUD, a 
little EPA, and a little EDA. But they're very

06:26.854 --> 06:28.315
different dialects. And I think we need to get the 
whole planning profession in general needs to get

06:29.957 --> 06:35.282
down a little bit. And be political. And know what 
you're doing. Be able to explain. And know in your

06:46.128 --> 06:49.272
head and in your heart, you know, what you're 
doing. And be able to explain these things to

06:49.733 --> 06:51.174
people. Don't sit back and make recommendations 
because somebody said so. You know, but I would

06:55.400 --> 07:07.455
much rather see a more general

06:55.400 --> 07:07.455
plan or come out of some of these things. Because I 
feel all of us were. I don't think anybody had any

07:09.558 --> 07:12.962
